Definition: a form of mercury poisoning among people who ate fish from mercury-contaminated waters of Minamata Bay off Japan in the 1950s
Example: characterized by severe neurological degeneration
Synonyms: mercury_poisoning, a, form, of, mercury, poisoning, among, people, who, ate, fish, from, mercury-contaminated, waters, Minamata, Bay, off, Japan, in, the, s, characterized, by, severe, neurological, degeneration
Category: noun.state
